\section{Refined Hodgkin--Huxley Model with Corrected Sodium Inactivation}

\subsection{State Space, Domain, and Units}

The state vector is
\[
(V, m, h, n) \in \mathbb{R} \times [0,1]^3,
\]
where $V$ is the membrane voltage (mV), and $m,h,n$ are gating probabilities.
The system follows the Hodgkin--Huxley formalism \cite{hodgkin1952quantitative}.

All parameters use the standard squid-axon convention:
\[
C_m \, [\mu\mathrm{F}/\mathrm{cm}^2], \quad
\bar g \, [\mathrm{mS/cm}^2], \quad
I \, [\mu\mathrm{A/cm}^2], \quad
\alpha_x,\beta_x \, [\mathrm{ms}^{-1}].
\]

\subsection{Membrane Potential Equation}

The membrane equation is given by conservation of charge:
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:dVdt}
C_m \frac{dV}{dt}
= I_{\mathrm{stim}}(t)
- \left[
\bar g_{\mathrm{Na}} m^3 h (V - E_{\mathrm{Na}})
+ \bar g_{\mathrm{K}} n^4 (V - E_{\mathrm{K}})
+ \bar g_{\mathrm{L}} (V - E_{\mathrm{L}})
\right].
\end{equation}

\subsection{Gating Variable Dynamics}

Each gating variable $x \in \{m,h,n\}$ satisfies:
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:dxdt}
\frac{dx}{dt} = \alpha_x(V) \left( 1 - x \right) - \beta_x(V) x.
\end{equation}

Steady state:
\[
x_\infty(V) = \frac{\alpha_x(V)}{\alpha_x(V) + \beta_x(V)}.
\]


